sub_topic: Prove that the complement of a set is unique.
message_1: Let A be a set with 10 elements and B be a subset of A with 6 elements. Find the number of elements in the complement of B in A.
message_2: The complement of B in A, denoted as A\B or A - B, consists of all the elements in A that are not in B. Since A has 10 elements and B has 6 elements, the complement of B in A has 10 - 6 = 4 elements.
